# VICE 3.9 → VICE 3.9 + SidVariant proxy layer
#
# Baseline: VICE 3.9 source tarball (https://vice-emu.sourceforge.io/index.html#download).
# Apply with:
#     cd vice-3.9/
#     patch -p1 < vice-sidvariant-v1.patch
#     ./autogen.sh && ./configure --enable-native-gtk3ui && make
#
# What this patch adds:
#
#   * Per-SID-chip "personality" layer driven by the SidVariant{,2..8} string
#     resources and the -sidvariant{,2..8} command-line flags.
#   * 10 built-in personalities:  armsid / arm2sid / swinu / swinnano /
#     fpgasid8580 / fpgasid6581 / pdsid / kungfusid-new / kungfusid-old /
#     backsid / skpico-8580 / skpico-6581 / sidfx / usid64 / none.
#     Each responds to the chip's detection magic-cookie protocol but does
#     not alter audio — ResID still synthesises the voice output.
#   * Gtk3 window title now shows "[SidVariant=<name>]" so the active
#     personality is visible at a glance.
#
# See docs/ARMSID_PROXY_PLAN.md in the siddetector2 repo for the full design
# rationale and phase breakdown.

